<paragraph base="F29577370" principles="yes" id="IFRS14_5"><paranum>5</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 14"/><data name="paranum" value="5"/></prolog><body><p id="IFRS14_P0017">An entity is permitted to apply the requirements of this Standard in its <xref base="F29577610" href="IFRS14_APPA.dita#IFRS14_APPA/IFRS14_DI0001" scope="local"><i>first IFRS financial statements</i><ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0133"/></ph></xref> if and only if it:</p><ol base="F29577373" type="lower-alpha" id="IFRS14_L0003"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value>         <p base="F29577374" id="IFRS14_P0018">conducts <xref base="F29577639" href="IFRS14_APPA.dita#IFRS14_APPA/IFRS14_DI0004" scope="local"><i>rate-regulated activities</i><ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0313"/></ph></xref>;                      and</p>       </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value>         <p base="F29577378" id="IFRS14_P0019">recognised amounts that qualify as <xref base="F29577655" href="IFRS14_APPA.dita#IFRS14_APPA/IFRS14_DI0007">regulatory deferral account balances<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0321"/></ph></xref> in its financial statements in accordance with its previous GAAP.</p>       </li></ol></body></paragraph>